    "body": "### Language server\n\n_No response_\n\n### Requested feature\n\nWhen working with repl, I have some utility buffers of the same type as the main files and the lsp server would generate many errors on them. I wish lsp can be turned off for such buffers.\r\n\r\nThe implementation could be simple. For instance, if a buffer is set with a local variable `b:lsp_disable`, then lsp would skip them. It would be nice if it is systematically implemented in nvim-lspconfig.\n\n### Other clients which have this feature\n\n_No response_",
