            "body": "Not sure if this is the typical way to do so, but can't find any other examples online, so a possibility for others who might land here; I wanted to disable the `sh` diagnostics for `.env` files:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal lsp_grp = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup(\"lsp_disable\", {clear = true})\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({\"BufEnter\", \"BufNewFile\"}, {\r\n    group = lsp_grp,\r\n    pattern = {\".env\", \".env.*\"},\r\n    callback = function()\r\n        vim.diagnostic.disable(0)\r\n    end\r\n})\r\n```",
            "created_at": "2023-03-30T00:58:10Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/2437#issuecomment-1489534767",
